    "Das and Balke (2022) show that each component in the decoding process might impact how biases are propagated into the generated responses.",
    "Thus, test scores may vary significantly for the same LLM, depending on the exact evaluation procedure.",
    "The wording of instructions and test items can also have strong impacts on model behavior.",
    "These manifold influences on test scores call for researchers to prioritize transparent and reproducible test use to allow for comparability between multiple studies.",
    "This includes the complete testing setup, e.g., model weights, in-and output formatting, and parameters of the generation process."
